# so-k02u: patch-package patches encode unified-diff context lines as a
# single space followed by the unchanged source content. A whitespace
# normalizer (e.g. a pre-commit hook stripping trailing spaces) corrupts
# blank context lines (" \n" → "\n") and patch-package then bails with
# "could not be parsed." Pin .patch files so git's whitespace handling
# (and any normalization driven via the whitespace attribute) leaves them
# byte-exact.
*.patch -whitespace
